CL:0000003.name: native cell
CL:0000003.clDescription: A cell that is found in a natural setting, which includes multicellular organism cells 'in vivo' (i.e. part of an organism), and unicellular organisms 'in environment' (i.e. part of a natural environment).

CL:0000037.name: hematopoietic stem cell
CL:0000037.clDescription: A stem cell from which all cells of the lymphoid and myeloid lineages develop, including blood cells and cells of the immune system. Hematopoietic stem cells lack cell markers of effector cells (lin-negative). Lin-negative is defined by lacking one or more of the following cell surface markers: CD2, CD3 epsilon, CD4, CD5 ,CD8 alpha chain, CD11b, CD14, CD19, CD20, CD56, ly6G, ter119.

CL:0000049.name: common myeloid progenitor
CL:0000049.clDescription: A progenitor cell committed to myeloid lineage, including the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages.
synonyms: colony forming unit granulocyte, erythrocyte, macrophage, and megakaryocyte

CL:0000050.name: megakaryocyte-erythroid progenitor cell
CL:0000050.clDescription: A progenitor cell committed to the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages.

CL:0000057.name: fibroblast
CL:0000057.clDescription: A connective tissue cell which secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules. Flattened and irregular in outline with branching processes; appear fusiform or spindle-shaped.

CL:0000064.name: ciliated cell
CL:0000064.clDescription: A cell that has a filiform extrusion of the cell surface.

CL:0000066.name: epithelial cell
CL:0000066.clDescription: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface. The cell has a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.

CL:0000067.name: ciliated epithelial cell
CL:0000067.clDescription: An epithelial cell that has a cilia.

CL:0000071.name: blood vessel endothelial cell
CL:0000071.clDescription: An endothelial cell that lines the vasculature.
synonyms: cuboidal endothelial cell of vascular tree

CL:0000077.name: mesothelial cell
CL:0000077.clDescription: A flattened epithelial cell of mesenchymal origin that lines the serous cavity.

CL:0000082.name: epithelial cell of lung
CL:0000082.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the lung.

CL:0000084.name: T cell
CL:0000084.clDescription: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

CL:0000097.name: mast cell
CL:0000097.clDescription: A cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation. Progenitors leave bone marrow and mature in connective and mucosal tissue. Mature mast cells are found in all tissues, except the bloodstream. Their phenotype is CD117-high, CD123-negative, CD193-positive, CD200R3-positive, and FceRI-high. Stem-cell factor (KIT-ligand; SCF) is the main controlling signal of their survival and development.

CL:0000115.name: endothelial cell
CL:0000115.clDescription: An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal. In mammals, endothelial cell has vimentin filaments and is derived from the mesoderm.

CL:0000125.name: glial cell
CL:0000125.clDescription: A non-neuronal cell of the nervous system. They not only provide physical support, but also respond to injury, regulate the ionic and chemical composition of the extracellular milieu. Guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons.

CL:0000134.name: mesenchymal stem cell
CL:0000134.clDescription: A connective tissue cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses. In humans, this cell type is CD73-positive, CD90-positive, CD105-positive, CD45-negative, CD34-negative, and MHCII-negative. They may further differentiate into osteoblasts, adipocytes, myocytes, neurons, or chondroblasts in vitro. Originally described as residing in the bone marrow, this cell type is now known to reside in many, if not all, adult organs.

CL:0000138.name: chondrocyte
CL:0000138.clDescription: Skeletogenic cell that is terminally differentiated, secretes an avascular, GAG-rich matrix, is embedded in cartilage tissue matrix, retains the ability to divide, and develops from a chondroblast cell.

CL:0000158.name: club cell
CL:0000158.clDescription: A non-mucous, epithelial secretory cell that is part of the tracheobronchial tree. A club cell has short microvilli but no cilia. A club cell is able to multiply and differentiate into ciliated cells to regenerate the bronchiolar epithelium and it also protects the tracheobronchial epithelium.

CL:0000160.name: goblet cell
CL:0000160.clDescription: A cell of the epithelial lining that produce and secrete mucins.

CL:0000164.name: enteroendocrine cell
CL:0000164.clDescription: An endocrine cell that is located in the epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract or in the pancreas.

CL:0000165.name: neuroendocrine cell
CL:0000165.clDescription: A neuron that is capable of some hormone secretion in response to neuronal signals.

CL:0000182.name: hepatocyte
CL:0000182.clDescription: The main structural component of the liver. They are specialized epithelial cells that are organized into interconnected plates called lobules. Majority of cell population of liver, polygonal in shape, arranged in plates or trabeculae between sinusoids; may have single nucleus or binucleated.

CL:0000183.name: contractile cell
CL:0000183.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to shorten.

CL:0000186.name: myofibroblast cell
CL:0000186.clDescription: An animal cell that has characteristics of both a fibroblast cell and a smooth muscle cell.

CL:0000187.name: muscle cell
CL:0000187.clDescription: A mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte. This cell has as part of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.

CL:0000192.name: smooth muscle cell
CL:0000192.clDescription: A non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the digestive tract, uterus, and blood vessels. They develop from specialized myoblasts (smooth muscle myoblast).

CL:0000209.name: taste receptor cell
CL:0000209.clDescription: A specialized cell involved in gustatory sensory perception.

CL:0000232.name: erythrocyte
CL:0000232.clDescription: A red blood cell. In mammals, mature erythrocytes are biconcave disks containing hemoglobin whose function is to transport oxygen.

CL:0000233.name: platelet
CL:0000233.clDescription: A non-nucleated disk-shaped cell formed by extrusion from megakaryocytes, found in the blood of all mammals, and mainly involved in blood coagulation.

CL:0000235.name: macrophage
CL:0000235.clDescription: A mononuclear phagocyte present in variety of tissues, typically differentiated from monocytes, capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.

CL:0000236.name: B cell
CL:0000236.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is capable of B cell mediated immunity.

CL:0000322.name: pneumocyte
CL:0000322.clDescription: An epithelial cell that lines the peripheral gas exchange region of the lungs of air-breathing vertebrates.

CL:0000359.name: vascular associated smooth muscle cell
CL:0000359.clDescription: A smooth muscle cell associated with the vasculature.

CL:0000451.name: dendritic cell
CL:0000451.clDescription: A cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation. These cells are lineage negative (CD3-negative, CD19-negative, CD34-negative, and CD56-negative).

CL:0000492.name: CD4-positive helper T cell
CL:0000492.clDescription: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that cooperates with other lymphocytes via direct contact or cytokine release to initiate a variety of immune functions.

CL:0000499.name: stromal cell
CL:0000499.clDescription: A connective tissue cell of an organ found in the loose connective tissue. These are most often associated with the uterine mucosa and the ovary as well as the hematopoietic system and elsewhere.

CL:0000540.name: neuron
CL:0000540.clDescription: The basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. Each neuron consists of a body, an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

CL:0000542.name: lymphocyte
CL:0000542.clDescription: A lymphocyte is a leukocyte commonly found in the blood and lymph that has the characteristics of a large nucleus, a neutral staining cytoplasm, and prominent heterochromatin.

CL:0000548.name: animal cell
CL:0000548.clDescription: A native cell that is part of some Metazoa.

CL:0000556.name: megakaryocyte
CL:0000556.clDescription: A large hematopoietic cell (50 to 100 micron) with a lobated nucleus. Once mature, this cell undergoes multiple rounds of endomitosis and cytoplasmic restructuring to allow platelet formation and release.

CL:0000557.name: granulocyte monocyte progenitor cell
CL:0000557.clDescription: A hematopoietic progenitor cell that is committed to the granulocyte and monocyte lineages. These cells are CD123-positive, and do not express Gata1 or Gata2 but do express C/EBPa, and Pu.1.
synonyms: CFU-C , Colony forming unit in culture

CL:0000558.name: reticulocyte
CL:0000558.clDescription: An immature erythrocyte that changes the protein composition of its plasma membrane by exosome formation and extrusion. The types of protein removed differ between species though removal of the transferrin receptor is apparent in mammals and birds.

CL:0000559.name: promonocyte
CL:0000559.clDescription: A precursor in the monocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between the monoblast and monocyte. This cell is CD11b-positive and has fine azurophil granules.

CL:0000576.name: monocyte
CL:0000576.clDescription: Myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

CL:0000583.name: alveolar macrophage
CL:0000583.clDescription: A tissue-resident macrophage found in the alveoli of the lungs. Ingests small inhaled particles resulting in degradation and presentation of the antigen to immunocompetent cells. Markers include F4/80-positive, CD11b-/low, CD11c-positive, CD68-positive, sialoadhesin-positive, dectin-1-positive, MR-positive, CX3CR1-negative.

CL:0000623.name: natural killer cell
CL:0000623.clDescription: A lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors and also regulate immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

CL:0000624.name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000624.clDescription: A mature alpha-beta T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD4 coreceptor.

CL:0000625.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000625.clDescription: A T cell expressing an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD8 coreceptor.

CL:0000646.name: basal cell
CL:0000646.clDescription: Undifferentiated; mitotic stem cell for other epithelial cell types; rounded or elliptical with little cytoplasm and few organelles; contain cytokeratin intermediate filament.

CL:0000650.name: mesangial cell
CL:0000650.clDescription: A cell type that encapsulates the capillaries and venules in the kidney. This cell secretes mesangial matrix that provides the structural support for the capillaries.

CL:0000653.name: podocyte
CL:0000653.clDescription: A specialized kidney epithelial cell, contained within a glomerulus, that contains "feet" that interdigitate with the "feet" of other podocytes.
synonyms: epithelial cell of visceral layer of glomerular capsule

CL:0000667.name: collagen secreting cell
CL:0000667.clDescription: An extracellular matrix secreting cell that secretes collagen.

CL:0000669.name: pericyte
CL:0000669.clDescription: An elongated, contractile cell found wrapped about precapillary arterioles outside the basement membrane. Pericytes are present in capillaries where proper adventitia and muscle layer are missing (thus distingushing this cell type from adventitial cells). They are relatively undifferentiated and may become fibroblasts, macrophages, or smooth muscle cells.

CL:0000731.name: urothelial cell
CL:0000731.clDescription: A cell of a layer of transitional epithelium in the wall of the proximal urethra, bladder, ureter or renal pelvis, external to the lamina propria.

CL:0000738.name: leukocyte
CL:0000738.clDescription: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

CL:0000763.name: myeloid cell
CL:0000763.clDescription: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.

CL:0000764.name: erythroid lineage cell
CL:0000764.clDescription: A immature or mature cell in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes.

CL:0000765.name: erythroblast
CL:0000765.clDescription: A nucleated precursor of an erythrocyte that lacks hematopoietic lineage markers.

CL:0000766.name: myeloid leukocyte
CL:0000766.clDescription: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, or mast cell lineage.

CL:0000767.name: basophil
CL:0000767.clDescription: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has an irregularly shaped, pale-staining nucleus that is partially constricted into two lobes, and with cytoplasm that contains coarse, bluish-black granules of variable size. Basophils contain vasoactive amines such as histamine and serotonin, which are released on appropriate stimulation. A basophil is CD123-positive, CD193-positive, CD203c-positive, and FceRIa-positive.

CL:0000771.name: eosinophil
CL:0000771.clDescription: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte with a nucleus that usually has two lobes connected by one or more slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing coarse, round granules that are uniform in size and which can be stained by the dye eosin. Eosinophils are CD9-positive, CD191-positive, and CD193-positive.

CL:0000775.name: neutrophil
CL:0000775.clDescription: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

CL:0000784.name: plasmacytoid dendritic cell
CL:0000784.clDescription: A dendritic cell type of distinct morphology, localization, and surface marker expression (CD123-positive) from other dendritic cell types and associated with early stage immune responses, particularly the release of physiologically abundant amounts of type I interferons in response to infection.

CL:0000786.name: plasma cell
CL:0000786.clDescription: A terminally differentiated, post-mitotic, antibody secreting cell of the B cell lineage with the phenotype CD138-positive, surface immunonoglobulin-negative, and MHC Class II-negative. Plasma cells are oval or round with extensive rough endoplasmic reticulum, a well-developed Golgi apparatus, and a round nucleus having a characteristic cartwheel heterochromatin pattern and are devoted to producing large amounts of immunoglobulin.

CL:0000787.name: memory B cell
CL:0000787.clDescription: A memory B cell is a mature B cell that is long-lived, readily activated upon re-encounter of its antigenic determinant, and has been selected for expression of higher affinity immunoglobulin. This cell type has the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, MHC Class II-positive, and CD138-negative.

CL:0000788.name: naive B cell
CL:0000788.clDescription: A naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, CD20-positive, CD27-negative and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

CL:0000789.name: alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000789.clDescription: A T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor complex.

CL:0000790.name: immature alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000790.clDescription: An alpha-beta T cell that has an immature phenotype and has not completed T cell selection.

CL:0000791.name: mature alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000791.clDescription: A alpha-beta T cell that has a mature phenotype.

CL:0000792.name: CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell
CL:0000792.clDescription: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta T cell that regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.
synonyms: CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T lymphocyte

CL:0000794.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta cytotoxic T cell
CL:0000794.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that is capable of killing target cells in an antigen specific manner with the phenotype perforin-positive and granzyme B-positive.

CL:0000798.name: gamma-delta T cell
CL:0000798.clDescription: A T cell that expresses a gamma-delta T cell receptor complex.

CL:0000810.name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta thymocyte
CL:0000810.clDescription: An immature alpha-beta T cell that is located in the thymus and is CD4-positive and CD8-negative.

CL:0000811.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta thymocyte
CL:0000811.clDescription: An immature alpha-beta T cell that is located in the thymus and is CD8-positive and CD4-negative.

CL:0000814.name: mature NK T cell
CL:0000814.clDescription: A mature alpha-beta T cell of a distinct lineage that bears natural killer markers and a T cell receptor specific for a limited set of ligands. NK T cells have activation and regulatory roles particularly early in an immune response.

CL:0000815.name: regulatory T cell
CL:0000815.clDescription: A T cell which regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.

CL:0000816.name: immature B cell
CL:0000816.clDescription: An immature B cell is a B cell that has the phenotype surface IgM-positive and surface IgD-negative, and have not undergone class immunoglobulin class switching or peripheral encounter with antigen and activation.

CL:0000817.name: precursor B cell
CL:0000817.clDescription: A precursor B cell is a B cell with the phenotype CD10-positive.

CL:0000820.name: B-1a B cell
CL:0000820.clDescription: A B-1 B cell that has the phenotype CD5-positive.

CL:0000821.name: B-1b B cell
CL:0000821.clDescription: A B-1 B cell that has the phenotype CD5-negative, but having other phenotypic attributes of a B-1 B cell.

CL:0000826.name: pro-B cell
CL:0000826.clDescription: A progenitor cell of the B cell lineage, with some lineage specific activity such as early stages of recombination of B cell receptor genes, but not yet fully committed to the B cell lineage until the expression of PAX5 occurs.

CL:0000836.name: promyelocyte
CL:0000836.clDescription: A precursor in the granulocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between a myeloblast and myelocyte, that has distinct nucleoli, a nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ratio of 5:1 to 3:1, and containing a few primary cytoplasmic granules. Markers for this cell are fucosyltransferase FUT4-positive, CD33-positive, integrin alpha-M-negative, low affinity immunoglobulin gamma Fc region receptor III-negative, and CD24-negative.

CL:0000842.name: mononuclear cell
CL:0000842.clDescription: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.

CL:0000844.name: germinal center B cell
CL:0000844.clDescription: A rapidly cycling mature B cell that has distinct phenotypic characteristics and is involved in T-dependent immune responses and located typically in the germinal centers of lymph nodes. This cell type expresses Ly77 after activation.

CL:0000860.name: classical monocyte
CL:0000860.clDescription: A monocyte that responds rapidly to microbial stimuli by secreting cytokines and antimicrobial factors and which is characterized by high expression of CCR2 in both rodents and humans, negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20, and of larger size than non-classical monocytes.

CL:0000861.name: elicited macrophage
CL:0000861.clDescription: A macrophage which develops from an inflammatory monocyte and is recruited into the tissues in response to injury and infection as part of an inflammatory response. Markers include CD11b-positive, CD68-positive, and F4/80-positive.

CL:0000875.name: non-classical monocyte
CL:0000875.clDescription: A type of monocyte characterized by low expression of CCR2, low responsiveness to monocyte chemoattractant CCL2/MCP1, low phagocytic activity, and decrease size relative to classical monocytes, but increased co-stimulatory activity. May also play a role in tissue repair.

CL:0000893.name: thymocyte
CL:0000893.clDescription: An immature T cell located in the thymus.

CL:0000895.name: naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000895.clDescription: An antigen inexperienced CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive and CD62L-positive. This cell type develops in the thymus. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high, and CD44-low.
synonyms: naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte

CL:0000898.name: naive T cell
CL:0000898.clDescription: Mature T cell not yet exposed to antigen with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD45RA-positive, and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

CL:0000899.name: T-helper 17 cell
CL:0000899.clDescription: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, and capable of producing IL-17.

CL:0000900.name: naive thymus-derived CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000900.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has not experienced activation via antigen contact and has the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CCR7-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.
synonyms: naive thymus-dervied CD8-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte

CL:0000905.name: effector memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000905.clDescription: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.
synonyms: effector CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T lymphocyte
effector memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte
effector CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell

CL:0000909.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell
CL:0000909.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has differentiated into a memory T cell.

CL:0000913.name: effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000913.clDescription: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.
synonyms: effector CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell
effector CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T lymphocyte
effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte

CL:0000931.name: activated type II NK T cell
CL:0000931.clDescription: A type II NK T cell that has been recently activated, secretes interferon-gamma and interleukin-4, and has the phenotype CD69-positive and downregulated NK markers.
synonyms: activated type II NK T lymphocyte

CL:0000936.name: early lymphoid progenitor
CL:0000936.clDescription: A lymphoid progenitor cell that is found in bone marrow, gives rise to B cells, T cells, natural killer cells and dendritic cells, and has the phenotype Lin-negative, Kit-positive, Sca-1-positive, FLT3-positive, CD34-positive, CD150 negative, and GlyA-negative.

CL:0000938.name: CD16-negative, CD56-bright natural killer cell, human
CL:0000938.clDescription: NK cell that has the phenotype CD56-bright, CD16-negative, and CD84-positive with the function to secrete interferon-gamma but is not cytotoxic.
synonyms: CD56-bright cytokine secreting natural killer cell

CL:0000939.name: CD16-positive, CD56-dim natural killer cell, human
CL:0000939.clDescription: A mature natural killer cell that has the phenotype CD56-low, CD16-positive and which is capable of cytotoxicity and cytokine production.

CL:0000940.name: mucosal invariant T cell
CL:0000940.clDescription: An alpha-beta T cell that is found in the lamina propria of mucosal tissues and is restricted by the MR-1 molecule.

CL:0000954.name: small pre-B-II cell
CL:0000954.clDescription: A small pre-B-II cell is a pre-B-II cell that is Rag1-positive, Rag2-positive, pre-BCR-negative, and BCR-negative, is not proliferating, and carries a DNA rearrangement of one or more immunoglobulin light chain genes.

CL:0000956.name: pre-B-I cell
CL:0000956.clDescription: A pre-B-I cell is a precursor B cell that expresses CD34 and surrogate immunoglobulin light chain (VpreB , Lambda 5 (mouse)/14.1 (human)) on the cell surface, and TdT, Rag1,and Rag2 intracellularly. Cell type carries a D-JH DNA rearrangement, and lacks expression of immunglobulin heavy chain protein.

CL:0000957.name: large pre-B-II cell
CL:0000957.clDescription: A large pre-B-II cell is a pre-B-II cell that is proliferating and is Rag1-negative and Rag2-negative.

CL:0000970.name: unswitched memory B cell
CL:0000970.clDescription: An unswitched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has the phenotype IgM-positive, IgD-positive, CD27-positive, CD138-negative, IgG-negative, IgE-negative, and IgA-negative.

CL:0000972.name: class switched memory B cell
CL:0000972.clDescription: A class switched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has undergone Ig class switching and therefore is IgM-negative on the cell surface. These cells are CD27-positive and have either IgG, IgE, or IgA on the cell surface.

CL:0000980.name: plasmablast
CL:0000980.clDescription: An activated mature (naive or memory) B cell that is secreting immunoglobulin, typified by being CD27-positive, CD38-positive, CD138-negative.

CL:0000985.name: IgG plasma cell
CL:0000985.clDescription: A fully differentiated plasma cell that secretes IgG.

CL:0000987.name: IgA plasma cell
CL:0000987.clDescription: A fully differentiated plasma cell that secretes IgA.

CL:0000990.name: conventional dendritic cell
CL:0000990.clDescription: Conventional dendritic cell is a dendritic cell that is CD11c-high.

CL:0001043.name: activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell, human
CL:0001043.clDescription: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.
synonyms: activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte, human

CL:0001044.name: effector CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0001044.clDescription: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

CL:0001054.name: CD14-positive monocyte
CL:0001054.clDescription: A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.

CL:0001056.name: dendritic cell, human
CL:0001056.clDescription: A dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive.

CL:0001057.name: myeloid dendritic cell, human
CL:0001057.clDescription: A myeloid dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive.

CL:0001058.name: plasmacytoid dendritic cell, human
CL:0001058.clDescription: A plasmacytoid dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD123-positive, and CD11c-negative.

CL:0001061.name: abnormal cell
CL:0001061.clDescription: A cell found in an organism or derived from an organism exhibiting a phenotype that deviates from the expected phenotype of any native cell type of that organism. Abnormal cells are typically found in disease states or disease models.

CL:0001062.name: effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell, terminally differentiated
CL:0001062.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha beta memory T cell with the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

CL:0001065.name: innate lymphoid cell
CL:0001065.clDescription: A lymphocyte that lacks characteristic T cell, B cell, myeloid cell, and dendritic cell markers, that functions as part of the innate immune response to produce cytokines and other effector responses.

CL:0001069.name: group 2 innate lymphoid cell
CL:0001069.clDescription: An innate lymphoid cell that is capable of producing T-helper 2-cell associated cytokines upon stimulation.

CL:0001071.name: group 3 innate lymphoid cell
CL:0001071.clDescription: An innate lymphoid cell that constituitively expresses RORgt and is capable of expressing IL17A and/or IL-22.

CL:0001074.name: CD34-positive, CD56-positive, CD117-positive common innate lymphoid precursor, human
CL:0001074.clDescription: An innate lymphoid cell precursor in the human with the phenotype CD34-positive, CD56-positive, CD117-positive.Thie cell type may include precusors to NK cells and ILC3 cells.

CL:0001203.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell, CD45RO-positive
CL:0001203.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with memory phenotype indicated by being CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.
synonyms: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T lymphocyte, CD45RO-positive

CL:0002038.name: T follicular helper cell
CL:0002038.clDescription: A CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cell located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that is BCL6-high, ICOS-high and PD1-high, and stimulates follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production.

CL:0002048.name: late pro-B cell
CL:0002048.clDescription: A pre-B cell precursor is CD19-low, CD22-positive , CD34-positive, CD38-positive.

CL:0002062.name: type I pneumocyte
CL:0002062.clDescription: A type I pneumocyte is a flattened, branched pneumocyte that covers more than 98% of the alveolar surface. This large cell has thin (50-100 nm) cytoplasmic extensions to form the air-blood barrier essential for normal gas exchange.

CL:0002063.name: type II pneumocyte
CL:0002063.clDescription: A type II pneumocyte is a pneumocyte that modulates the fluid surrounding the alveolar epithelium by secreting and recycling surfactants. This cell type also contributes to tissue repair and can differentiate after injury into a type I pneumocyte. Thicker than squamous alveolar cells, have a rounded apical surface that projects above the level of surrounding epithelium. The free surface is covered by short microvilli.

CL:0002075.name: brush cell of trachebronchial tree
CL:0002075.clDescription: Infrequent type of columnar epithelial cell. This cell is characterized by the presence of a tuft of blunt, squat microvilli (approximately 120-140/cell) on the cell surface. The microvilli contain filaments that stretch into the underlying cytoplasm. They have a distinctive pear shape with a wide base and a narrow microvillous apex. Function not known.

CL:0002092.name: bone marrow cell
CL:0002092.clDescription: A cell found in the bone marrow. This can include fibroblasts, macrophages, adipocytes, osteoblasts, osteoclasts, endothelial cells and hematopoietic cells.

CL:0002138.name: endothelial cell of lymphatic vessel
CL:0002138.clDescription: A endothelial cell of a lymphatic vessel. The border of the oak leaf-shaped endothelial cell of initial lymphatics are joined by specialized buttons. The discontinuous feature of buttons distinguishes them from zippers in collecting lymphatics, but both types of junctions are composed of proteins typical of adherens junctions and tight junctions found in the endothelium of blood vessels. Buttons seal the sides of flaps of the oak leaf-shaped endothelial cell, leaving open the tips of flaps as routes for fluid entry without disassembly and reformation of intercellular junctions.

CL:0002139.name: endothelial cell of vascular tree
CL:0002139.clDescription: An endothelial cell of the vascular tree, which includes blood vessels and lymphatic vessels.
synonyms: cubodial endothelial cell of vascular tree

CL:0002144.name: capillary endothelial cell
CL:0002144.clDescription: An endothelial cell found in capillaries.

CL:0002188.name: glomerular endothelial cell
CL:0002188.clDescription: An endothelial cell found in the glomerulus of the kidney. This cell is flattened, highly fenestrated, and plays a vital role in the formation of glomerular ultrafiltrate.

CL:0002201.name: renal beta-intercalated cell
CL:0002201.clDescription: A renal intercalated cell that secretes base and reabsorbs acid in the distal segments of the kidney tubule to maintain acid/base balance.

CL:0002241.name: pulmonary interstitial fibroblast
CL:0002241.clDescription: A fibroblasts found in interstitial spaces in the pulmonary tract. Greater numbers of these cells are found in idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis.

CL:0002306.name: epithelial cell of proximal tubule
CL:0002306.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the proximal tubule of the kidney.

CL:0002319.name: neural cell
CL:0002319.clDescription: A cell that is part of the nervous system.

CL:0002328.name: bronchial epithelial cell
CL:0002328.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the bronchus.

CL:0002355.name: primitive red blood cell
CL:0002355.clDescription: A large nucleated basophilic erythrocyte found in mammalian embryos. This cell type arises from the blood islands of yolk sacs and expresses different types of hemoglobins (beta-H1, gamma-1 and zeta) than adult erythrocytes. Considered a type of erythroblast as this cell type can enucleate in circulation.

CL:0002368.name: respiratory epithelial cell
CL:0002368.clDescription: An endo-epithelial cell of the respiratory tract.

CL:0002375.name: Schwann cell precursor
CL:0002375.clDescription: A giioblast cell that develops from a migratory neural crest cell. The SCP is embedded among neurons (axons) with minimal extracellular spaces separating them from nerve cell membranes and has no basal lamina. In rodents SCPs are the only cells in the Schwann cell linage that expresses Cdh19.

CL:0002377.name: immature Schwann cell
CL:0002377.clDescription: A glial cell that develops from a Schwann cell precursor. The immature Schwann cell is embedded among neurons (axons) with minimal extracellular spaces separating them from nerve cell membranes and has a basal lamina. Cells can survive without an axon present. Immature Schwann cell can be found communally ensheathing large groups of axons.

CL:0002393.name: intermediate monocyte
CL:0002393.clDescription: A monocyte that has characteristics of both patrolling and inflammatory monocytes.

CL:0002397.name: CD14-positive, CD16-positive monocyte
CL:0002397.clDescription: A CD14-positive monocyte that is also CD16-positive and CCR2-negative.

CL:0002399.name: CD1c-positive myeloid dendritic cell
CL:0002399.clDescription: A myeloid dendritic cell found in the blood that is CD1c-positive.

CL:0002470.name: MHC-II-positive classical monocyte
CL:0002470.clDescription: Gr1-high monocyte that has a MHC-II receptor complex.

CL:0002518.name: kidney epithelial cell
CL:0002518.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the kidney.

CL:0002543.name: vein endothelial cell
CL:0002543.clDescription: An endothelial cell that is part of the vein.

CL:0002553.name: fibroblast of lung
CL:0002553.clDescription: A fibroblast that is part of lung.

CL:0002563.name: intestinal epithelial cell
CL:0002563.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the intestine.

CL:0002573.name: Schwann cell
CL:0002573.clDescription: A glial cell that myelinates or ensheathes axons in the peripheral nervous system.

CL:0002632.name: epithelial cell of lower respiratory tract

CL:0002633.name: respiratory basal cell
CL:0002633.clDescription: A basal cell in the respiratory tract.

CL:0005009.name: renal principal cell
CL:0005009.clDescription: A cuboidal epithelial cell of the kidney which regulates sodium and potassium balance. The activity of sodium and potassium channels on the apical membrane of the cell is regulated by aldosterone and vasopressin. In mammals this cell type is located in the renal collecting duct system.

CL:0005010.name: renal intercalated cell
CL:0005010.clDescription: A cuboidal epithelial cell of the kidney that regulates acid/base balance.

CL:0005011.name: renal alpha-intercalated cell
CL:0005011.clDescription: A cuboidal epithelial cell of the kidney which secretes acid and reabsorbs base to regulate acid/base balance.

CL:0005025.name: visceromotor neuron
CL:0005025.clDescription: A motor neuron that synapses to parasympathetic neurons that innervate tear glands, sweat glands, and the smooth muscles and glands of the pulmonary, cardiovascular, and gastrointestinal systems.

CL:0008019.name: mesenchymal cell
CL:0008019.clDescription: A non-polarised cell precursor cell that is part of some mesenchyme, is associated with the cell matrix but is not connected to other cells and is capable of migration.

CL:0010003.name: epithelial cell of alveolus of lung
CL:0010003.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part_of a alveolus of lung.

CL:0011020.name: neural progenitor cell
CL:0011020.clDescription: An undifferentiated cell that originates from a neural stem cell and has the capacity to generate multiple types of lineage-restricted progenitors but not to self-renew.

CL:0011026.name: progenitor cell
CL:0011026.clDescription: A precursor cell that has a tendency to differentiate into a specific type of cell. They are descendants of stem cells, only they are more constrained in their differentiation potential or capacity for self-renewal, and are often more limited in both senses.

CL:0017000.name: pulmonary ionocyte
CL:0017000.clDescription: An ionocyte that is part of the lung epithelium. The cells from this type are major sources of the CFTR protein in human and mice.

CL:0019001.name: tracheobronchial serous cell
CL:0019001.clDescription: Any serous secreting cell that is part of the tracheobronchial epithelium.

CL:0019019.name: tracheobronchial smooth muscle cell
CL:0019019.clDescription: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the tracheobronchial tree.
synonyms: smooth muscle cell of tracheobronchial tree

CL:1000413.name: endothelial cell of artery
CL:1000413.clDescription: A blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of an arterial endothelium.

CL:1000449.name: epithelial cell of nephron
CL:1000449.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of the nephron.

CL:1000452.name: parietal epithelial cell
CL:1000452.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of the glomerular parietal epithelium.
synonyms: epithelial cell of parietal layer of glomerular capsule

CL:1000491.name: mesothelial cell of pleura
CL:1000491.clDescription: A mesothelial cell that is part of the pleura.

CL:1000597.name: papillary tips cell
CL:1000597.clDescription: A cell that is part of a tip of a renal papilla.

CL:1000698.name: kidney resident macrophage
CL:1000698.clDescription: A tissue-resident macrophage that is part of some kidney.

CL:1000849.name: kidney distal convoluted tubule epithelial cell

CL:1000909.name: kidney loop of Henle epithelial cell

CL:1001016.name: kidney loop of Henle ascending limb epithelial cell

CL:1001106.name: kidney loop of Henle thick ascending limb epithelial cell
CL:1001106.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thick ascending limb. It is known in some mammalian species that this cell may express the Na+-K+-2Cl− cotransporter (NKCC2) apically.

CL:1001107.name: kidney loop of Henle thin ascending limb epithelial cell
CL:1001107.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thin ascending limb.

CL:1001111.name: kidney loop of Henle thin descending limb epithelial cell
CL:1001111.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thin descending limb.

CL:1001131.name: vasa recta ascending limb cell
CL:1001131.clDescription: A cell that is part of some vasa recta ascending limb.

CL:1001285.name: vasa recta descending limb cell
CL:1001285.clDescription: A cell that is part of some vasa recta descending limb.

CL:1001318.name: renal interstitial pericyte
CL:1001318.clDescription: A pericyte cell located in the kidney interstitium.

CL:1001603.name: lung macrophage
CL:1001603.clDescription: Circulating macrophages and tissue macrophages (alveolar macrophages) of lung.

CL:2000032.name: peripheral nervous system neuron
CL:2000032.clDescription: A neuron that is part of a peripheral nervous system.

CL:2000093.name: bronchus fibroblast of lung
CL:2000093.clDescription: Any fibroblast of lung that is part of a bronchus.

CL:4023054.name: mesothelial fibroblast
CL:4023054.clDescription: A mesothelial cell that has undergone mesothelial-to-mesenchymal transition (MMT) to become a fibroblast cell.

CL:4028006.name: alveolar type 2 fibroblast cell
CL:4028006.clDescription: A pulmonary interstitial fibroblast that is part of the alveolus and localizes to vascular adventitia.

CL:4030009.name: epithelial cell of proximal tubule segment 1
CL:4030009.clDescription: Epithelial cell that is part of segment 1 (S1) of the proximal tubule epithelium.
synonyms: epithelial cell of segment 1 of proximal tubule

CL:4030011.name: epithelial cell of proximal tubule segment 3
CL:4030011.clDescription: Epithelial cell that is part of segment 3 (S3) of the proximal tubule epithelium.
synonyms: epithelial cell of segment 3 of proximal tubule

CL:4030018.name: kidney connecting tubule principal cell
CL:4030018.clDescription: A renal principal cell located in the connecting tubule.

CL:0000000.name: cell
CL:0000000.clDescription: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

CL:0000034.name: stem cell
CL:0000034.clDescription: A relatively undifferentiated cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

CL:0000035.name: single fate stem cell
CL:0000035.clDescription: A stem cell that self-renews as well as give rise to a single mature cell type.

CL:0000048.name: multi fate stem cell
CL:0000048.clDescription: A stem cell that can give rise to multiple lineages of cells.

CL:0000055.name: non-terminally differentiated cell
CL:0000055.clDescription: A precursor cell with a limited number of potential fates.

CL:0000068.name: duct epithelial cell
CL:0000068.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of a duct.

CL:0000075.name: columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell
CL:0000075.clDescription: A columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface. Columnar/cuboidal epithelial cells take on the shape of a column or cube.

CL:0000081.name: blood cell
CL:0000081.clDescription: A cell found predominately in the blood.

CL:0000094.name: granulocyte
CL:0000094.clDescription: A leukocyte with abundant granules in the cytoplasm.

CL:0000098.name: sensory epithelial cell
CL:0000098.clDescription: A specialized epithelial cell involved in sensory perception. Restricted to special sense organs of the olfactory, gustatory, and vestibulocochlear receptor systems; contain sensory cells surrounded by supportive, non-receptive cells.

CL:0000100.name: motor neuron
CL:0000100.clDescription: An efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes or inhibits movement.

CL:0000145.name: professional antigen presenting cell
CL:0000145.clDescription: A cell capable of processing and presenting lipid and protein antigens to T cells in order to initiate an immune response.

CL:0000150.name: glandular epithelial cell
CL:0000150.clDescription: A specialized epithelial cell that is capable of synthesizing and secreting certain biomolecules.

CL:0000151.name: secretory cell
CL:0000151.clDescription: A cell that specializes in controlled release of one or more substances.

CL:0000157.name: surfactant secreting cell
CL:0000157.clDescription: A cell that specializes in secretion of surfactant in the alveoli of the lung.

CL:0000163.name: endocrine cell
CL:0000163.clDescription: A cell of an endocrine gland, ductless glands that secrete substances which are released directly into the circulation and which influence metabolism and other body functions.

CL:0000197.name: sensory receptor cell
CL:0000197.clDescription: A cell that is capable of detection of a stimulus involved in sensory perception.

CL:0000206.name: chemoreceptor cell
CL:0000206.clDescription: A cell specialized to detect chemical substances and relay that information centrally in the nervous system. Chemoreceptors may monitor external stimuli, as in taste and olfaction, or internal stimuli, such as the concentrations of oxygen and carbon dioxide in the blood.

CL:0000211.name: electrically active cell
CL:0000211.clDescription: A cell whose function is determined by the generation or the reception of an electric signal.

CL:0000213.name: lining cell
CL:0000213.clDescription: A cell within an epithelial cell sheet whose main function is to act as an internal or external covering for a tissue or an organism.

CL:0000215.name: barrier cell
CL:0000215.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to prevent the transport of stuff across compartments.

CL:0000219.name: motile cell
CL:0000219.clDescription: A cell that moves by its own activities.

CL:0000225.name: anucleate cell
CL:0000225.clDescription: A cell that lacks a nucleus.

CL:0000226.name: single nucleate cell
CL:0000226.clDescription: A cell with a single nucleus.

CL:0000234.name: phagocyte
CL:0000234.clDescription: Any cell capable of ingesting particulate matter via phagocytosis.

CL:0000244.name: transitional epithelial cell
CL:0000244.clDescription: A cell characteristically found lining hollow organs that are subject to great mechanical change due to contraction and distention; originally thought to represent a transition between stratified squamous and columnar epithelium.

CL:0000393.name: electrically responsive cell
CL:0000393.clDescription: A cell whose function is determined by its response to an electric signal.

CL:0000404.name: electrically signaling cell
CL:0000404.clDescription: A cell that initiates an electrical signal and passes that signal to another cell.

CL:0000412.name: polyploid cell
CL:0000412.clDescription: A cell whose nucleus, or nuclei, each contain more than two haploid genomes.

CL:0000424.name: excretory cell
CL:0000424.clDescription: A cell involved in the elimination of metabolic and foreign toxins, and in maintaining the ionic, acid-base and water balance of biological fluids.

CL:0000473.name: defensive cell
CL:0000473.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to protect the organism.

CL:0000527.name: efferent neuron
CL:0000527.clDescription: A neuron which sends impulses peripherally to activate muscles or secretory cells.

CL:0000630.name: supporting cell
CL:0000630.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to support other cell types.

CL:0000710.name: neurecto-epithelial cell
CL:0000710.clDescription: Epithelial cells derived from neural plate and neural crest.

CL:0000723.name: somatic stem cell
CL:0000723.clDescription: A stem cell that can give rise to cell types of the body other than those of the germ-line.

CL:0000782.name: myeloid dendritic cell
CL:0000782.clDescription: A dendritic cell of the myeloid lineage.

CL:0000785.name: mature B cell
CL:0000785.clDescription: A B cell that is mature, having left the bone marrow. Initially, these cells are IgM-positive and IgD-positive, and they can be activated by antigen.

CL:0000813.name: memory T cell
CL:0000813.clDescription: A long-lived, antigen-experienced T cell that has acquired a memory phenotype including distinct surface markers and the ability to differentiate into an effector T cell upon antigen reexposure.

CL:0000819.name: B-1 B cell
CL:0000819.clDescription: A B cell of distinct lineage and surface marker expression. B-1 B cells are thought to be the primary source of natural IgM immunoglobulin, that is, IgM produced in large quantities without prior antigenic stimulation and generally reactive against various microorganisms, as well as the source of T-independent IgA immunoglobulin in the mucosal areas. These cells are CD43-positive.

CL:0000824.name: mature natural killer cell
CL:0000824.clDescription: A natural killer cell that is developmentally mature and expresses a variety of inhibitory and activating receptors that recognize MHC class I and other stress related molecules.

CL:0000837.name: hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell
CL:0000837.clDescription: A hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell is multipotent, but not capable of long-term self-renewal. These cells are characterized as lacking lineage cell surface markers and being CD34-positive in both mice and humans.

CL:0000838.name: lymphoid lineage restricted progenitor cell
CL:0000838.clDescription: A progenitor cell restricted to the lymphoid lineage.

CL:0000839.name: myeloid lineage restricted progenitor cell
CL:0000839.clDescription: A progenitor cell restricted to the myeloid lineage.

CL:0000864.name: tissue-resident macrophage
CL:0000864.clDescription: A macrophage constitutively resident in a particular tissue under non-inflammatory conditions, and capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.

CL:0000896.name: activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000896.clDescription: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

CL:0000897.name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell
CL:0000897.clDescription: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has differentiated into a memory T cell.

CL:0000911.name: effector T cell
CL:0000911.clDescription: A differentiated T cell with ability to traffic to peripheral tissues and is capable of mounting a specific immune response.

CL:0000922.name: type II NK T cell
CL:0000922.clDescription: An alpha-beta T cell expressing NK call markers that is CD1d restricted and expresses a diverse TCR repertoire. Type II NKT cells do not become activated by alpha-galactosylceramide when presented by CD1d.

CL:0000945.name: lymphocyte of B lineage
CL:0000945.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage with the commitment to express an immunoglobulin complex.

CL:0000946.name: antibody secreting cell
CL:0000946.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is devoted to secreting large amounts of immunoglobulin.

CL:0000955.name: pre-B-II cell
CL:0000955.clDescription: A pre-B-II cell is a precursor B cell that expresses immunoglobulin mu heavy chain (IgHmu+), and lack expression of CD34, TdT, immunoglobulin kappa light chain and immunoglobulin lambda light chain.

CL:0000974.name: long lived plasma cell
CL:0000974.clDescription: A fully differentiated plasma cell that lives for years, as opposed to months, secretes immunoglobulin, and has the phenotype weakly CD19-positive, CD20-negative, CD38-negative, strongly CD138-positive, MHC Class II-negative, surface immunoglobulin-negative, IgD-negative, and strongly CXCR4-positive. The majority of these cells of this type reside in the bone marrow.

CL:0000988.name: hematopoietic cell
CL:0000988.clDescription: A cell of a hematopoietic lineage.

CL:0001012.name: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor OR granulocyte monocyte progenitor

CL:0001019.name: CD115-positive monocyte OR common dendritic progenitor

CL:0001022.name: CD115-positive monocyte
CL:0001022.clDescription: CD115-positive monocyte is a monocyte that is CD115-positive and CD11b-positive.

CL:0001035.name: bone cell
CL:0001035.clDescription: A connective tissue cell found in bone.

CL:0001060.name: hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell, lineage-negative
CL:0001060.clDescription: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities. Cell lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

CL:0001067.name: group 1 innate lymphoid cell
CL:0001067.clDescription: An innate lymphoid cell that is capable of producing the type 1 cytokine IFN-gamma, but not Th2 or Th17 cell-associated cytokines.

CL:0001082.name: immature innate lymphoid cell
CL:0001082.clDescription: An innate lyphoid cell with an immature phenotype.

CL:0001200.name: lymphocyte of B lineage, CD19-positive
CL:0001200.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is CD19-positive.

CL:0001201.name: B cell, CD19-positive
CL:0001201.clDescription: A B cell that is CD19-positive.

CL:0001204.name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell, CD45RO-positive
CL:0001204.clDescription: CD4-positive, alpha-beta long-lived T cell with the phenotype CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.
synonyms: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T lymphocyte, CD45RO-positive

CL:0000313.name: serous secreting cell
CL:0000313.clDescription: Columnar glandular cell with irregular nucleus, copious granular endoplasmic reticulum and supranuclear granules. Secretes a watery fluid containing proteins known as serous fluid.

CL:0000325.name: stuff accumulating cell
CL:0000325.clDescription: A cell that is specialised to accumulate a particular substance(s).

CL:0002031.name: hematopoietic lineage restricted progenitor cell
CL:0002031.clDescription: A hematopoietic progenitor cell that is capable of developing into only one lineage of hematopoietic cells.

CL:0002032.name: hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell
CL:0002032.clDescription: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities.

CL:0002076.name: endo-epithelial cell
CL:0002076.clDescription: An epithelial cell derived from endoderm.

CL:0002077.name: ecto-epithelial cell
CL:0002077.clDescription: An epithelial cell derived from ectoderm.

CL:0002078.name: meso-epithelial cell
CL:0002078.clDescription: Epithelial cell derived from mesoderm or mesenchyme.

CL:0002191.name: granulocytopoietic cell
CL:0002191.clDescription: A cell involved in the formation of a granulocyte.

CL:0002194.name: monopoietic cell
CL:0002194.clDescription: A cell involved in the formation of a monocyte (monopoiesis).

CL:0002202.name: epithelial cell of tracheobronchial tree
CL:0002202.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the tracheobronchial tree.

CL:0002204.name: brush cell
CL:0002204.clDescription: A cell type found in the gastrointestinal and respiratory tracts that is characterized by the presence of a tuft of blunt, squat microvilli (120-140 per cell). Function of this cell type is not known.

CL:0002242.name: nucleate cell
CL:0002242.clDescription: A cell containing at least one nucleus.

CL:0002251.name: epithelial cell of alimentary canal
CL:0002251.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the musculomembranous digestive tube extending from the mouth to the anus.

CL:0002274.name: histamine secreting cell
CL:0002274.clDescription: A cell type that secretes histamine.

CL:0002305.name: epithelial cell of distal tubule
CL:0002305.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the distal convoluted tubule of the kidney that helps regulate systemic levels of potassium, sodium, calcium, and pH.

CL:0002417.name: primitive erythroid lineage cell
CL:0002417.clDescription: An immature or mature cell of the first erythroid lineage to arise during embryonic development.

CL:0002419.name: mature T cell
CL:0002419.clDescription: A T cell that expresses a T cell receptor complex and has completed T cell selection.

CL:0002420.name: immature T cell
CL:0002420.clDescription: A T cell that has not completed T cell selection.

CL:0002522.name: renal filtration cell
CL:0002522.clDescription: A renal filtration cell is a specialized cell of the renal system that filter fluids by charge, size or both.

CL:0002584.name: renal cortical epithelial cell
CL:0002584.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the kidney cortex.

CL:0005006.name: ionocyte
CL:0005006.clDescription: Specialized epithelial cells involved in the maintenance of osmotic homeostasis. They are characterized by abundant mitochondria and ion transporters. In amniotes, they are present in the renal system. In freshwater fish, ionocytes in the skin and gills help maintain osmotic homeostasis by absorbing salt from the external environment.

CL:0008034.name: mural cell
CL:0008034.clDescription: Mural cells are pericytes and the vascular smooth muscle cells (vSMCs) of the microcirculation.

CL:0011115.name: precursor cell
CL:0011115.clDescription: A cell that, by division or terminal differentiation, can give rise to other cell types.

CL:0002320.name: connective tissue cell
CL:0002320.clDescription: A cell of the supporting or framework tissue of the body, arising chiefly from the embryonic mesoderm and including adipose tissue, cartilage, and bone.

CL:0002370.name: respiratory goblet cell
CL:0002370.clDescription: A simple columnar epithelial cell that secretes mucin. Rough endoplasmic reticulum, mitochondria, the nucleus, and other organelles are concentrated in the basal portion. The apical plasma membrane projects microvilli to increase surface area for secretion.

CL:0002371.name: somatic cell
CL:0002371.clDescription: A cell of an organism that does not pass on its genetic material to the organism's offspring (i.e. a non-germ line cell).

CL:0002395.name: Gr1-high classical monocyte
CL:0002395.clDescription: A resident monocyte that is Gr-1 high, CD43-negative, CX3CR1-negative, CD115-positive, and B220-negative.

CL:1000450.name: epithelial cell of glomerular capsule
CL:1000450.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of the glomerular capsule.

CL:1000453.name: epithelial cell of intermediate tubule
CL:1000453.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of the intermediate tubule.

CL:1000454.name: kidney collecting duct epithelial cell
CL:1000454.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of the collecting duct of renal tubule.
synonyms: epithelial cell of renal collecting tubule

CL:1000494.name: nephron tubule epithelial cell
CL:1000494.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of a nephron tubule.

CL:1001021.name: kidney loop of Henle descending limb epithelial cell

CL:1001610.name: bone marrow hematopoietic cell
CL:1001610.clDescription: Hematopoietic cells resident in the bone marrow. Include: hematopoietic stem cells (lymphoid stem cells and myeloid stem cells) and the precursor cells for thrombocytes, erythrocytes, basophils, neutrophils, eosinophils, monocytes and lymphocytes.

CL:2000008.name: microvascular endothelial cell
CL:2000008.clDescription: Any blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of a microvascular endothelium.

CL:0008000.name: non-striated muscle cell
CL:0008000.clDescription: Any muscle cell in which the fibers are not organised into sarcomeres.

CL:0008001.name: hematopoietic precursor cell
CL:0008001.clDescription: Any hematopoietic cell that is a precursor of some other hematopoietic cell type.

CL:0008007.name: visceral muscle cell
CL:0008007.clDescription: A muscle cell that is part of some visceral muscle.

CL:4030002.name: effector memory CD45RA-positive, alpha-beta T cell, terminally differentiated
CL:4030002.clDescription: An alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CD45RA-positive.
synonyms: terminally differentiated effector memory cells re-expressing CD45RA
terminally differentiated effector memory CD45RA+ T cells

CL:4030031.name: interstitial cell
CL:4030031.clDescription: Any cell that is located within the interstitium between the cells most prominent in defining a given tissue. "Interstitial cell" is a morphological term and refers to a variety of cells with differing origins and phenotypes.

CL:4030034.name: respiratory ciliated cell
CL:4030034.clDescription: A ciliated cell of the respiratory system. Ciliated cells are present in airway epithelium.
synonyms: ciliated cell of the respiratory tract
